1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:02,138
So when are you coming back?

2
00:00:02,138 --> 00:00:03,911
I'll be gone for two days and will be back soon.

3
00:00:03,911 --> 00:00:07,082
I promise that I'll be a good boy down there.

4
00:00:07,082 --> 00:00:09,420
Khru Prince is sick. Ai Aou took over and is nursing him in our place.

5
00:00:09,420 --> 00:00:12,540
Don't let him be alone with Ai Aou. Got it?

6
00:00:12,540 --> 00:00:14,732
Are you the one Kuafah met on the mountain?

7
00:00:14,732 --> 00:00:17,031
I'm Kitty, his girlfriend.

8
00:00:17,031 --> 00:00:18,794
Some girl suddenly called my number.

9
00:00:18,794 --> 00:00:20,074
Khru Prince took the call.

10
00:00:20,074 --> 00:00:23,421
I will be so happy if you can climb the Himalayas again.

11
00:00:23,421 --> 00:00:28,309
If that person can inspire you to climb again, don't let that person go.

12
00:00:28,309 --> 00:00:30,318
I'm back.

13
00:00:30,318 --> 00:00:31,955
You.

14
00:00:35,058 --> 00:00:38,315
Don't you have to celebrate your brother's birthday?

15
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:41,925
My little brother has got something urgent to do

16
00:00:41,925 --> 00:00:46,030
so he postponed the party. That's why I hurried back.

17
00:00:46,030 --> 00:00:47,669
Oh.

18
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:53,757
Hey. About last night...

19
00:00:53,757 --> 00:00:56,154
Khru Prince, we have a situation.

20
00:00:56,154 --> 00:00:58,045
Viah and Sompor are fighting.

21
00:00:58,045 --> 00:00:59,545
What?

22
00:01:07,580 --> 00:01:14,190
[Mek JirakitThawornwong | Mark Jiruntanin Trairattanayon]

23
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:19,320
♫ Taking a journey, no matter how far the horizon ♫

24
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:24,090
♫ No matter how high or steep the mountain ♫

25
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:32,000
♫ But in the end, it's too late, love vanished ♫

26
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:36,490
♫ Until I met you halfway ♫

27
00:01:36,490 --> 00:01:40,930
♫ Just like that, the sky brightened ♫

28
00:01:40,930 --> 00:01:49,900
♫ Don't know why when you're close, it gives me the strength to keep walking ♫

29
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:54,890
♫ Do you think that our love really exists? ♫

30
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:57,880
[Star and Sky│Sky in your heart]

31
00:01:57,880 --> 00:02:00,800
[Series Director: Siwat Sawatmaneekul]

32
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:10,350
Sompor, do you have anything to say to Viah?

33
00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:13,792
I'm sorry, Viah.

34
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:17,915
Viah, do you have anything to say?

35
00:02:17,915 --> 00:02:20,788
I'm not wrong. Why should I say sorry?

36
00:02:20,788 --> 00:02:24,265
Viah, I heard the story from Sompor.

37
00:02:24,265 --> 00:02:27,016
She said you broke your word.

38
00:02:27,016 --> 00:02:32,113
At first, you said you would buy her a birthday gift.

39
00:02:32,113 --> 00:02:36,659
But you bought gifts for other girls, too. Is that right?

40
00:02:37,336 --> 00:02:41,062
But I don't think Viah did anything wrong.

41
00:02:41,062 --> 00:02:42,381
What?

42
00:02:42,381 --> 00:02:47,711
He promised to buy her a present

43
00:02:47,711 --> 00:02:49,737
and he did.

44
00:02:49,737 --> 00:02:53,867
Buying things for other people at the same time isn't breaking the promise.

45
00:02:53,867 --> 00:02:57,448
That's right. Why are you angry?

46
00:02:58,201 --> 00:03:02,124
Viah, this is about feelings.

47
00:03:02,124 --> 00:03:06,641
Though you didn't mean to, you made her upset.

48
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,800
Aren't you going to say sorry?

49
00:03:15,138 --> 00:03:18,669
Upsetting someone and not apologizing...

50
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:25,000
you'll be a bad adult when you get older.

51
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:29,420
Are you talking about me?

52
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:32,481
I'm not. I was talking to Viah.

53
00:03:32,481 --> 00:03:36,380
You were talking to Viah, but I saw you looking at me just now.

54
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:41,494
If you did nothing wrong, you have nothing to worry about.

55
00:03:41,494 --> 00:03:44,220
See? You were talking about me.

56
00:03:44,220 --> 00:03:46,150
I said I was talking about the children.

57
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,862
Why is it so hard for you to understand?

58
00:03:47,862 --> 00:03:52,074
Talking about the children? Then why did you say he would grow up to be a bad adult?

59
00:03:52,074 --> 00:03:53,615
You're clearly referring to me.

60
00:03:53,615 --> 00:03:55,820
Calm down.

61
00:04:26,978 --> 00:04:30,120
Happy birthday, Dao.

62
00:04:33,803 --> 00:04:36,129
Thank you.

63
00:04:44,886 --> 00:04:47,973
I wish you a very good year.

64
00:04:50,725 --> 00:04:55,136
It's already good because you're with me.

65
00:04:58,555 --> 00:05:02,300
But let me sleep ten more minutes, please.

66
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,042
Of course.

67
00:05:20,997 --> 00:05:23,339
If the children didn't stop me,

68
00:05:23,339 --> 00:05:25,030
I'd definitely fight him.

69
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:26,832
Do you guys get me?

70
00:05:26,832 --> 00:05:28,443
I do.

71
00:05:28,443 --> 00:05:30,117
But I think you're still at fault this time.

72
00:05:30,117 --> 00:05:32,073
You even had a guilty conscience.

73
00:05:32,073 --> 00:05:33,273
What?

74
00:05:33,273 --> 00:05:36,904
You promised him before you left you would behave.

75
00:05:36,904 --> 00:05:41,180
But you got wasted, and that girl called and harassed him.

76
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:45,255
Is this what you call a good adult?

77
00:05:45,255 --> 00:05:48,900
Well, I made a small mistake.

78
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:54,181
Besides, he and I aren't a thing.

79
00:05:54,181 --> 00:05:56,062
You get me, don't you, Ai Mesa?

80
00:05:56,062 --> 00:05:58,262
I do.

81
00:05:58,262 --> 00:06:01,400
But if he's nothing to you, why the heck did you give him the promise?

82
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,000
What?

83
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,625
You guys are my friends. How about you take my side?

84
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:07,667
No.

85
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:12,848
Someone like you will never change, no matter how much time passes.

86
00:06:12,848 --> 00:06:14,748
You're never regretful.

87
00:06:14,748 --> 00:06:17,855
I think you better go and make it up to him.

88
00:06:19,315 --> 00:06:21,194
How would I do that?

89
00:06:21,194 --> 00:06:25,960
Just seeing him today, he was emitting anger toward me.

90
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:28,028
Like this.

91
00:06:28,028 --> 00:06:31,211
I just do what you do best and fib.

92
00:06:31,211 --> 00:06:32,995
Like pretend to get sick.

93
00:06:32,995 --> 00:06:35,468
So he can feel pity for you.

94
00:06:38,042 --> 00:06:41,638
You're onto something... Did you say I like to lie?

95
00:06:41,638 --> 00:06:43,845
Did you just realize that?

96
00:06:43,845 --> 00:06:45,071
Anyway,

97
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:49,305
I think you should pretend to be sick tomorrow.

98
00:06:49,305 --> 00:06:54,022
I'll spread the news to the children, and they'll tell Khru Prince.

99
00:06:54,022 --> 00:06:58,422
It's more reliable that way. He will believe you're really sick.

100
00:07:03,045 --> 00:07:05,619
Gosh! Does Dr. Fah have a serious stomachache?

101
00:07:05,619 --> 00:07:08,252
Keep it between us. Otherwise it'll cause panic.

102
00:07:08,252 --> 00:07:10,569
Trust me on that.

103
00:07:10,569 --> 00:07:12,262
Hot news!

104
00:07:12,262 --> 00:07:14,820
What? Is Dr. Fah pregnant?

105
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:16,520
What?

106
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:23,116
Khru Prince. Khru Prince.

107
00:07:23,116 --> 00:07:28,007
Is it true that Dr. Fah is sick, and you are pregnant?

108
00:07:28,007 --> 00:07:30,900
Sompor.

109
00:07:31,949 --> 00:07:36,563
I think there are some misunderstandings here.

110
00:07:41,184 --> 00:07:44,900
Khun. Khun.

111
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:48,700
Were you the one to spread the rumor to the children?

112
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:50,531
Hey!

113
00:07:50,531 --> 00:07:52,731
P'JJ.

114
00:07:52,731 --> 00:07:54,581
Why are you here?

115
00:07:54,581 --> 00:07:56,480
Khru Prince.

116
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,983
I was just watching the place for Kuafah.

117
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:04,431
And where is he?

118
00:08:04,431 --> 00:08:07,876
He has a stomachache. He's resting at his house alone.

119
00:08:07,876 --> 00:08:09,854
Poor him.

120
00:08:09,854 --> 00:08:12,022
He's a doctor.

121
00:08:12,022 --> 00:08:16,231
But when a doctor gets sick, no one takes care of him.

122
00:08:25,756 --> 00:08:28,674
It's me. Are you in?

123
00:08:30,066 --> 00:08:32,428
I am.

124
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:44,163
I brought you congee and antacid medicine.

125
00:08:44,163 --> 00:08:47,337
I heard you had acid reflux.

126
00:08:47,337 --> 00:08:49,264
Thank you.

127
00:08:51,595 --> 00:08:52,797
Are you okay?

128
00:08:52,797 --> 00:08:55,597
I am.

129
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,300
You don't look okay at all.

130
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:07,899
Here. Let me help.

131
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,908
Can you eat it?

132
00:09:41,908 --> 00:09:44,636
Of course. It's good.

133
00:10:38,074 --> 00:10:41,688
After taking the medicine, get some rest.

134
00:10:41,688 --> 00:10:43,215
I'll just leave now.

135
00:10:43,215 --> 00:10:45,015
Hold on.

136
00:10:46,844 --> 00:10:49,337
I have something to say to you.

137
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:54,266
What is it?

138
00:10:55,165 --> 00:10:56,665
Well...

139
00:10:57,409 --> 00:11:00,366
I want to explain about the other night.

140
00:11:01,636 --> 00:11:04,036
You don't have to. Just get some rest.

141
00:11:04,036 --> 00:11:05,402
I can't do that.

142
00:11:05,402 --> 00:11:09,519
If I don't get this out, I won't be able to sleep.

143
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:13,949
That night, I didn't mean to go out and get drunk.

144
00:11:13,949 --> 00:11:19,735
My brother's boyfriend took me there.

145
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:24,187
And how old are you now? Don't you know how to say no?

146
00:11:24,187 --> 00:11:26,356
I went out just to drink.

147
00:11:26,356 --> 00:11:29,561
I just didn't think I'd be that drunk.

148
00:11:29,561 --> 00:11:35,674
And the girl who called you took my phone when I was using the restroom.

149
00:11:35,674 --> 00:11:39,766
What she said was all nonsense. She isn't my girlfriend.

150
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:45,486
Actually, her relation to you has nothing to do with me.

151
00:11:45,486 --> 00:11:47,586
It does.

152
00:11:47,586 --> 00:11:49,755
You're angry at me.

153
00:11:50,387 --> 00:11:51,968
I'm not.

154
00:11:51,968 --> 00:11:53,300
You are.

155
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:55,913
I can tell from your voice you're furious.

156
00:11:55,913 --> 00:11:58,380
If I didn't pretend I was sick to get you here,

157
00:11:58,380 --> 00:12:01,269
I wouldn't know you're this angry.

158
00:12:01,269 --> 00:12:02,669
Oh, no!

159
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:07,340
It's not that. I mean...

160
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:09,269
Do you think I'm that silly?

161
00:12:09,269 --> 00:12:11,193
I didn't mean it that way.

162
00:12:11,193 --> 00:12:15,022
I just don't want you to be jealous over nonsense.

163
00:12:15,734 --> 00:12:17,179
You're so damn...

164
00:12:17,179 --> 00:12:19,848
Besides being a jerk, you're also a narcissist.

165
00:12:21,257 --> 00:12:22,840
What a waste of time.

166
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:26,368
Hey. Khun!

167
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:30,630
[Ban Khun Om Haet Nok School]

168
00:12:38,246 --> 00:12:41,300
P'Mesa, did you forget something?

169
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:45,609
No. I came to talk to you.

170
00:12:45,609 --> 00:12:49,149
I heard you guys had a fight.

171
00:12:50,088 --> 00:12:53,437
Yes. It's quite bad.

172
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:57,897
That's what I heard.

173
00:12:57,897 --> 00:13:01,097
If you want my help, feel free to ask.

174
00:13:02,806 --> 00:13:04,536
Are you sure?

175
00:13:04,536 --> 00:13:07,519
Of course. I know both parties.

176
00:13:07,519 --> 00:13:10,894
I don't want you guys to avoid each other.

177
00:13:11,589 --> 00:13:15,569
I'd like to ask you one thing then.

178
00:13:22,179 --> 00:13:27,029
Can you please hand this letter to the Village Headman for me?

179
00:13:27,029 --> 00:13:31,086
Oh, wow. You wanted to write a letter to my friend so much—

180
00:13:31,086 --> 00:13:33,991
Wait. The Village Headman?

181
00:13:33,991 --> 00:13:40,125
That's right. I wrote a letter asking permission to organize a sports day event in the village.

182
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:41,583
A sports day?

183
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:44,834
Because of the fight between Viah and Sompor,

184
00:13:44,834 --> 00:13:50,477
I got the idea to amend their relationship.

185
00:13:50,477 --> 00:13:55,057
Then the fight you mentioned...

186
00:13:55,057 --> 00:13:59,482
- It's between Viah and Sompor.
- Viah and Sompor?

187
00:13:59,482 --> 00:14:00,982
Yes.

188
00:14:01,746 --> 00:14:04,021
So is this the letter for the Village Headman?

189
00:14:04,021 --> 00:14:05,884
Yes.

190
00:14:05,884 --> 00:14:07,510
Got it.

191
00:14:07,510 --> 00:14:09,080
I understand.

192
00:14:12,777 --> 00:14:16,382
So Khru Prince is only concerned about the children fighting.

193
00:14:16,382 --> 00:14:19,210
He doesn't even care about you at all.

194
00:14:19,210 --> 00:14:22,438
Yes, damn it. I'm so pissed.

195
00:14:22,438 --> 00:14:25,467
How do I patch things up with him?

196
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:26,806
I already faked my sickness.

197
00:14:26,806 --> 00:14:30,049
How about you fake your death this time?

198
00:14:30,049 --> 00:14:32,272
Maybe he'll forgive you.

199
00:14:32,272 --> 00:14:35,475
Oh, yes. That's a smart idea.

200
00:14:37,091 --> 00:14:38,500
Fah!

201
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,821
All right then.

202
00:14:39,821 --> 00:14:41,524
How on earth did you come up with that?

203
00:14:41,524 --> 00:14:44,046
One more scoop, please.

204
00:14:44,046 --> 00:14:48,734
I think you should help him with the sports day thing.

205
00:14:48,734 --> 00:14:50,593
That way you can be close to him.

206
00:14:50,593 --> 00:14:52,277
That's right. Good idea.

207
00:14:52,277 --> 00:14:56,246
Show him your hard work. He might come around.

208
00:14:56,246 --> 00:14:57,746
That's right.

209
00:14:58,381 --> 00:15:00,971
All right, I'll give it a try.

210
00:15:00,971 --> 00:15:03,832
Thank you guys so much. Here is your reward.

211
00:15:07,050 --> 00:15:11,421
The children should be so proud to have such a caring teacher.

212
00:15:12,124 --> 00:15:16,384
No. You're the one who cares about them.

213
00:15:16,384 --> 00:15:18,270
You've brought them lots of snacks.

214
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:20,417
They should be so happy.

215
00:15:20,417 --> 00:15:23,820
I'm happy, too, to see you smile.

216
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:29,069
I mean I'm happy to see the children smile.

217
00:15:38,968 --> 00:15:42,385
Excuse me. You've got the paint there.

218
00:15:50,697 --> 00:15:52,397
Okay.

219
00:15:55,456 --> 00:15:58,064
Hey, Dr. Fah.

220
00:15:58,948 --> 00:16:01,145
Are you here to help?

221
00:16:01,849 --> 00:16:03,729
Yes.

222
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:07,609
But I see you have enough people helping.

223
00:16:07,609 --> 00:16:10,605
- You probably don't need me.
- It's not enough.

224
00:16:10,605 --> 00:16:13,938
There's a lot left to do. Please come.

225
00:16:18,754 --> 00:16:20,234
Here.

226
00:16:20,234 --> 00:16:21,862
Sure.

227
00:16:21,862 --> 00:16:24,823
Where should I paint?

228
00:16:24,823 --> 00:16:27,479
That's not for painting. Please clean it for me.

229
00:16:27,479 --> 00:16:29,895
I will change the colors to paint.

230
00:16:31,466 --> 00:16:33,750
Let's not bother him.

231
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:35,650
He's a doctor.

232
00:16:35,650 --> 00:16:38,444
He has to take care of many people.

233
00:16:40,051 --> 00:16:41,894
I can do it.

234
00:16:41,894 --> 00:16:44,933
Unless someone doesn't want me to.

235
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:47,350
Everyone wants your help.

236
00:16:47,350 --> 00:16:50,624
There's a lot left to do. Please help.

237
00:16:50,624 --> 00:16:52,523
Sure.

238
00:16:52,523 --> 00:16:55,074
Thanks for having me.

239
00:16:57,503 --> 00:17:01,347
Everyone has a piece of paper with the team color on it.

240
00:17:01,347 --> 00:17:05,154
According to the lucky draw, there will be the blue and the white team.

241
00:17:05,154 --> 00:17:07,910
Open it and see.

242
00:17:18,528 --> 00:17:23,057
You can split into your teams and practice for the competition.

243
00:17:23,057 --> 00:17:24,680
Hold on.

244
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:28,209
The children said they wanted you to compete, too.

245
00:17:28,950 --> 00:17:30,810
- Would that be okay?
- Of course.

246
00:17:30,810 --> 00:17:34,682
I will join, too. The more the merrier.

247
00:17:34,682 --> 00:17:38,399
- Is that right?
- Right.

248
00:17:39,742 --> 00:17:41,142
See?

249
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:43,580
That's good.

250
00:17:43,580 --> 00:17:46,949
Ai JJ and I will also compete then.

251
00:17:46,949 --> 00:17:48,697
You didn't even ask me.

252
00:17:48,697 --> 00:17:51,082
Come on. Just help me.

253
00:18:01,328 --> 00:18:03,614
All right then.

254
00:18:03,614 --> 00:18:05,286
We have some papers left.

255
00:18:05,286 --> 00:18:06,986
Please draw one.

256
00:18:16,431 --> 00:18:17,870
Which color are you?

257
00:18:17,870 --> 00:18:20,067
Blue. You?

258
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,616
I got blue, too.

259
00:18:21,616 --> 00:18:23,389
We're on the same team.

260
00:18:23,389 --> 00:18:26,469
Can I call it destiny?

261
00:18:27,685 --> 00:18:30,975
This is not a very good start at all.

262
00:18:36,508 --> 00:18:38,946
The sports day will be held next week, right?

263
00:18:38,946 --> 00:18:42,005
It sounds really fun.

264
00:18:42,005 --> 00:18:46,217
That's right. The children were so excited today.

265
00:18:47,088 --> 00:18:49,134
But we're not on the same team.

266
00:18:49,134 --> 00:18:50,834
